South African Cleaning Workers to Strike on Aug. 8 Over Wages, Union Says

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-08-03T16:55:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/south-african-cleaning-workers-to-strike-on-aug-8-over-wages-union-says.html
South African contract cleaners plan
to go on strike on Aug. 8 after wage talks with employers failed
to reach an agreement, according to the South African Transport
and Allied Workers Union.  Satawu and other unions “have served the employers with a
48 hours’ notice of intentions to strike,” the Johannesburg-
based union said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  